climbs.name: Humpty Hump
climbs.fa: Unknown (assume it's been climbed before; not on MP; Chris Reynolds 8/9/2020)

content.description: Start is at the base of the honeycomb. Possibly two cruxes: first is the large hump in the middle of the route, second is the overhung finish. The hump *may* require a small dyno to pass the top off some small-ish crimps and a sidepull on the left. The overhang at the top has some semi-decent hands, though the slots are pitched slightly downward toward the front.
content.protection: Large trees directly above for setting static line
content.location: Face directly to the left of the dihedral; between the dihedral edge and the twin flakes.Â

climbs.name: Fishlips
climbs.fa: Unknown (assume it's been climbed before; not on MP; Chris Reynolds and Jim Arnold climbed it 8/9/2020)

content.description: Start is from the left (south) side of the off-width crack. Good hands and feet through the traverse to the left (north) under the "wave" overhang. Crux is the finish, which is over the ceiling. Not sure the grade is right yet; please provide feedback!
content.protection: There are several large trees at the top to set static lines
content.location: Around the corner after passing the large, lichen-covered slab due south of Owl's Eyes/Shooting Star. There is "FISH" spray painted at the base right next to a large off-width crack

content.description: Vertical with some slabby sections. Relatively smooth sandstone mixed in with significant honeycomb formations, with an overhanging "wave" at the northern end. Shaded.
